FBIS4-12960 "drnes073_r_94003" FBIS-NES-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 SOUTH ASIA India Two Punjab `Militants' Killed; Weapons Recovered Two Punjab `Militants' Killed; Weapons Recovered BK1504062194 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network in English 1630 GMT 14 Apr 94 BK1504062194 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network English BFN [Text] In a major success in antiterrorist operations, the acting chief of the so-called Khalistan Commando Force, Punjab Singh, and an accomplice were killed this morning in an encounter with the security forces in Punjab's Tarn Taran District. He is responsible for more than 100 killings, including two bus massacres. Sixteen AK-47 rifles, one machine gun and one wireless set were recovered from the truck in which the militants were traveling.
